text.tspan: Share of potential polio cases with adequate stool collection, 2001
This is an indicator of testing for polio. It shows the share of acute flaccid paralysis (AFP) cases that were tested for poliovirus and
Note: The WHO recommends that the adequate stool collection rate should be at least 80% to ensure that suspected cases are being tested sufficiently.
